('grp_b3434dcffb654aec8b5938f53f0a040b', 'Let the pig die', 'Pork is one of the most widely consumed and versatile meats in the world, valued for its rich flavor, tenderness, and adaptability in countless culinary traditions. Derived from domesticated pigs, pork offers a wide range of cuts, each with unique textures and tastes — from the succulent tenderness of pork tenderloin to the flavorful richness of bacon and ribs. It can be roasted, grilled, fried, smoked, or stewed, making it a staple ingredient in cuisines across Asia, Europe, Africa, and the Americas. Beyond its savory appeal, pork is also a good source of high-quality protein, essential vitamins like B6 and B12, and important minerals such as zinc, iron, and phosphorus, all of which support muscle growth and overall body health. When prepared properly, pork can be both delicious and nutritious. Traditional dishes such as roasted pork belly, pulled pork, sweet and sour pork, and barbecued spare ribs highlight its culinary diversity. Modern chefs often use pork in gourmet creations, balancing its natural fattiness with herbs, spices, and marinades. Whether served in a festive meal or a simple family dinner, pork continues to be celebrated as a comforting, flavorful, and satisfying source of nourishment around the world.', 'Post relevant information', 'open', '', '', 'archived', '2025-10-21 11:48:30', 'grp_b3434dcffb654aec8b5938f53f0a040b', 'yes', 'brb99446033cea4a1bb3ed01507e611ced', NULL, NULL, '2025-10-21 13:59:13'),
